 hours on end to raise their sseru faction.  With some knowledge of the story behind this quest one would conclude that this is false and killing the rescusos is not needed.  It would seem logical to me that Torsten is on Katta Faction, perhaps Validos Custodus.<br>
<br>
As far as faction needed.  I have tried to get earing one twice now.  I was threateningly with torsten and used sneak (im a monk) to raise my faction to indifferent.  I gave the bixie charm to torsten and got his text saying &quot;here is the note to bregun&quot; but the note did NOT appear in my inventory.  I then did the quest over again with the same faction and got the SAME result.  I'm thinking you MUST have indifferent or higher faction to get earing 1.  Indifferent without invis/sneak/hide that is.<br>
<br>
I'll be working on the 4reports FIRST before I get the first earing.  Why?  I need Validos Custodos faction for the first earing.  Killing the guards the drop the reports im assuming give +validos custodos faction and therefore I'll be killing two birds with one stone.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
P.S-I would not read the previous threads on this topic.  They will confuse you more then anything.  The only thing I'd like to add is that you can kill bregun for the bixie charm.  I think everything else is pretty nicely summed up in the first post in this thread....<br>
<br>
